{"questionId":"2604647","questionHtml":"<p>Hence or otherwise, find the shortest distance from&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi></math> to <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>L</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></math>.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p><strong>METHOD 1</strong></p>\n<p>recognizing shortest distance from <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi></math> is perpendicular to <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>L</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></math><strong>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;</strong><em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>OR&nbsp;&nbsp;<img src=\"__IMG__/1e55348cc5353e86af6b966a4788179c7742b11f.png\">&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>sin</mi><mfrac><mi>π</mi><mn>3</mn></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mi>x</mi><mfenced open=\"|\" close=\"|\"><mover><mi>PA</mi><mo>→</mo></mover></mfenced></mfrac></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced open=\"|\" close=\"|\"><mover><mi>PA</mi><mo>→</mo></mover></mfenced><mo>=</mo><msqrt><msup><mn>6</mn><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><msup><mn>6</mn><mn>2</mn></msup></msqrt></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mo>=</mo><msqrt><mn>72</mn></msqrt><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>6</mn><msqrt><mn>2</mn></msqrt></mrow></mfenced></math> (seen anywhere)<strong>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;</strong><em><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><msqrt><mn>3</mn></msqrt><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mi>x</mi><msqrt><mn>72</mn></msqrt></mfrac></math><strong>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;</strong><em><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><em><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><msqrt><mn>216</mn></msqrt><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mo>=</mo><msqrt><mn>54</mn></msqrt><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>3</mn><msqrt><mn>6</mn></msqrt></mrow></mfenced></math></em></p>\n<p>shortest distance is <em><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><msqrt><mn>216</mn></msqrt><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mo>=</mo><msqrt><mn>54</mn></msqrt><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>3</mn><msqrt><mn>6</mn></msqrt></mrow></mfenced></math><strong>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;</strong></em><strong><em>A1</em></strong></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>METHOD 2</strong></p>\n<p>recognition that the distance required is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mfenced open=\"|\" close=\"|\"><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"bold-italic\">v</mi><mo>+</mo><mover><mi>PA</mi><mo>→</mo></mover></mrow></mfenced><mfenced open=\"|\" close=\"|\"><mi mathvariant=\"bold-italic\">v</mi></mfenced></mfrac></math><strong>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;</strong><em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><msqrt><mn>2</mn></msqrt></mfrac><mfenced open=\"|\" close=\"|\"><mrow><mfenced><mtable><mtr><mtd><mn>1</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mn>1</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mn>0</mn></mtd></mtr></mtable></mfenced><mo>×</mo><mfenced><mtable><mtr><mtd><mn>6</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mn>0</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mn>6</mn></mtd></mtr></mtable></mfenced></mrow></mfenced><mo>&nbsp;</mo></math><strong>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;</strong><em><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><msqrt><mn>2</mn></msqrt></mfrac><mfenced open=\"|\" close=\"|\"><mfenced><mtable><mtr><mtd><mn>6</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mo>-</mo><mn>6</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mo>-</mo><mn>6</mn></mtd></mtr></mtable></mfenced></mfenced><mo>&nbsp;</mo></math><strong>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;</strong><em><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>shortest distance is&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msqrt><mn>54</mn></msqrt><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mo>=</mo><mn>3</mn><msqrt><mn>6</mn></msqrt></mrow></mfenced></math><strong>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;</strong><em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:right;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:left;\"><strong>METHOD 3<br></strong></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:left;\">recognition that the base of the triangle is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mfenced open=\"|\" close=\"|\"><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"bold-italic\">v</mi><mo>·</mo><mover><mi>PA</mi><mo>→</mo></mover></mrow></mfenced><mfenced open=\"|\" close=\"|\"><mi mathvariant=\"bold-italic\">v</mi></mfenced></mfrac></math><strong>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;</strong><em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><msqrt><mn>2</mn></msqrt></mfrac><mfenced open=\"|\" close=\"|\"><mrow><mfenced><mtable><mtr><mtd><mn>1</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mn>1</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mn>0</mn></mtd></mtr></mtable></mfenced><mo>·</mo><mfenced><mtable><mtr><mtd><mn>6</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mn>0</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mn>6</mn></mtd></mtr></mtable></mfenced></mrow></mfenced><mo>&nbsp;</mo></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>6</mn><msqrt><mn>2</mn></msqrt></mfrac><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>(</mo><mo>=</mo><mn>3</mn><msqrt><mn>2</mn></msqrt><mo>)</mo></math> OR <img src=\"__IMG__/9156a0ffb289dae3b0af7ecdb44f12b33cff5c87.png\"><strong>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;</strong><em><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced open=\"|\" close=\"|\"><mover><mi>PA</mi><mo>→</mo></mover></mfenced><mo>=</mo><msqrt><msup><mn>6</mn><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><msup><mn>6</mn><mn>2</mn></msup></msqrt></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mo>=</mo><msqrt><mn>72</mn></msqrt><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>6</mn><msqrt><mn>2</mn></msqrt></mrow></mfenced></math> (seen anywhere)<strong>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;</strong><em><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong>&nbsp;The value of&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced open=\"|\" close=\"|\"><mover><mi>PA</mi><mo>→</mo></mover></mfenced><mo>=</mo><msqrt><msup><mn>6</mn><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><msup><mn>6</mn><mn>2</mn></msup></msqrt></math>&nbsp;may be seen as part of the working of their shortest distance,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>d</mi><mo>=</mo><msqrt><mfenced open=\"|\" close=\"|\"><mover><mi>PA</mi><mo>→</mo></mover></mfenced><mo>-</mo><msup><mi>b</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></msqrt><mo>=</mo><msqrt><msup><mfenced><msqrt><mn>72</mn></msqrt></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><msup><mfenced><mrow><mn>3</mn><msqrt><mn>2</mn></msqrt></mrow></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup></msqrt></math></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>shortest distance is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msqrt><mn>54</mn></msqrt><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mo>=</mo><mn>3</mn><msqrt><mn>6</mn></msqrt></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:right;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:left;\"><strong>METHOD 4<br></strong></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:left;\">Let&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi></math> be a general point on <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>L</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></math> <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>(</mo><mi>λ</mi><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>8</mn><mo>+</mo><mi>λ</mi><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>)</mo></math> such that <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>AB</mi></math> is perpendicular to <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>L</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></math></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:left;\">attempt to find vector <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mover><mi>AB</mi><mo>→</mo></mover></math> OR <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced open=\"|\" close=\"|\"><mover><mi>AB</mi><mo>→</mo></mover></mfenced></math> (the shortest distance from <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi></math> to <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>L</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></math>)&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:left;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mover><mi>AB</mi><mo>→</mo></mover><mo>=</mo><mover><mi>OB</mi><mo>→</mo></mover><mo>-</mo><mover><mi>OA</mi><mo>→</mo></mover><mo>=</mo><mover><mi>OP</mi><mo>→</mo></mover><mo>+</mo><mi>λ</mi><mfenced><mtable><mtr><mtd><mn>1</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mn>1</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mn>0</mn></mtd></mtr></mtable></mfenced><mo>-</mo><mover><mi>OA</mi><mo>→</mo></mover><mfenced><mrow><mo>=</mo><mfenced><mtable><mtr><mtd><mn>0</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mn>8</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn></mtd></mtr></mtable></mfenced><mo>+</mo><mi>λ</mi><mfenced><mtable><mtr><mtd><mn>1</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mn>1</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mn>0</mn></mtd></mtr></mtable></mfenced><mo>-</mo><mfenced><mtable><mtr><mtd><mn>6</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mn>8</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mn>3</mn></mtd></mtr></mtable></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mover><mrow><mtext>A</mtext><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi></mrow><mo>→</mo></mover><mo>+</mo><mi>λ</mi><mfenced><mtable><mtr><mtd><mn>1</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mn>1</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mn>0</mn></mtd></mtr></mtable></mfenced></mrow></mfenced><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mi>λ</mi><mo>∈</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">ℝ</mi></mrow></mfenced></math></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:left;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mover><mi>AB</mi><mo>→</mo></mover><mo>=</mo><mfenced><mtable><mtr><mtd><mo>-</mo><mn>6</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mn>0</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mo>-</mo><mn>6</mn></mtd></mtr></mtable></mfenced><mo>+</mo><mi>λ</mi><mfenced><mtable><mtr><mtd><mn>1</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mn>1</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mn>0</mn></mtd></mtr></mtable></mfenced></math>&nbsp; OR&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced open=\"|\" close=\"|\"><mover><mi>AB</mi><mo>→</mo></mover></mfenced><mo>=</mo><msqrt><msup><mfenced><mrow><mi>λ</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>6</mn></mrow></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><msup><mfenced><mrow><mn>8</mn><mo>+</mo><mi>λ</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>8</mn></mrow></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><msup><mfenced><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn></mrow></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup></msqrt></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:left;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced open=\"|\" close=\"|\"><mover><mi>AB</mi><mo>→</mo></mover></mfenced><mo>=</mo><msqrt><msup><mfenced><mrow><mi>λ</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>6</mn></mrow></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><msup><mi>λ</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><msup><mfenced><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>6</mn></mrow></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup></msqrt><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mo>=</mo><msqrt><mn>2</mn><msup><mi>λ</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mn>12</mn><mi>λ</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>72</mn></msqrt></mrow></mfenced></math></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:left;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:left;\"><strong>EITHER</strong></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:left;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi><mi>λ</mi></mrow></mfrac><mfenced><msup><mfenced open=\"|\" close=\"|\"><mover><mi>AB</mi><mo>→</mo></mover></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>⇒</mo><mn>4</mn><mi>λ</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>12</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>⇒</mo><mi>λ</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>3</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:left;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:left;\"><strong>OR</strong></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:left;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced open=\"|\" close=\"|\"><mover><mi>AB</mi><mo>→</mo></mover></mfenced><mo>=</mo><msqrt><mn>2</mn><msup><mfenced><mrow><mi>λ</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn></mrow></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>54</mn></msqrt></math> to obtain <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>λ</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>3</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:left;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:left;\"><strong>OR</strong></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:left;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mtable><mtr><mtd><mo>-</mo><mn>6</mn><mo>+</mo><mi>λ</mi></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mi>λ</mi></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mo>-</mo><mn>6</mn></mtd></mtr></mtable></mfenced><mo>·</mo><mfenced><mtable><mtr><mtd><mn>1</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mn>1</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mn>0</mn></mtd></mtr></mtable></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>⇒</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>6</mn><mo>+</mo><mi>λ</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>λ</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>⇒</mo><mi>λ</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>3</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:left;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:left;\"><strong>THEN</strong></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:left;\">shortest distance is&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msqrt><mn>54</mn></msqrt><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mo>=</mo><mn>3</mn><msqrt><mn>6</mn></msqrt></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:left;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:left;\"><em><strong>[4 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"2604647","referenceCode":"23M.1.AHL.TZ1.12c","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Hence or otherwise, find the shortest distance from A to L1.","paper":"1","level":"HL","questionNumber":"c","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 4]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 2—Functions","Topic 3— Geometry and trigonometry","Topic 3— Geometry and trigonometry","SL 3.2—2d and 3d trig, sine rule, cosine rule, area","Topic 3— Geometry and trigonometry","AHL 3.13—Scalar (dot) product","Topic 2—Functions","SL 2.7—Solutions of quadratic equations and inequalities, discriminant and nature of roots"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}